      • schedule

        private static <T> long schedule(boolean sync,
                                 T obj,
                                 java.util.function.Consumer<T> operation,
                                 long wait,
                                 int count)
                          throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                                 java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Schedules a task. All tasks will be executed on their own thread, so as to prevent other tasks from being prevented from running.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input to the operation.
        Parameters:
        sync - true if each task execution must finish before the next execution can begin, false otherwise.
        obj - the object to execute the operation on.
        operation - the consumer operation to execute.
        wait - how long to wait before initially executing the task in milliseconds, and how long to wait before executing the task again if it executes more than once. To have the task be executed immediately, use ScheduledTask.INSTANTANEOUS.
        count - the amount of times the task should be executed. To have the task be executed indefinitely, use ScheduledTask.INFINITE.
        Returns:
        the task ID.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the command is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the execution count is less than zero and not equal to .

        public static <T> long scheduleSync(T obj,
                                    java.util.function.Consumer<T> operation,
                                    long wait,
                                    int count)
                             throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                                    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Schedules a task. All tasks will be executed on their own thread, so as to prevent other tasks from being prevented from running. If the task executes multiple times however, the next execution will not begin until the one before it is finished.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input to the operation.
        Parameters:
        obj - the object to execute the operation on.
        operation - the consumer operation to execute.
        wait - how long to wait before initially executing the task, and how long to wait before executing the task again if it executes more than once. To have the task be executed immediately, use ScheduledTask.INSTANTANEOUS.
        count - the amount of times the task should be executed. To have the task be executed indefinitely, use ScheduledTask.INFINITE.
        Returns:
        the task ID.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the operation is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the execution count is less than zero and not equal to .
        See Also:
        scheduleAsync(Object, Consumer, long, int)

      • cancelTask

        public static boolean cancelTask(long taskId)
        Cancels a task. This allows for infinitely repeating tasks to be ended or to prevent a task from ever executing in the first place after it has been scheduled.
        Parameters:
        taskId - the ID of the task to cancel.
        Returns:
        true if the task was successfully cancelled, false otherwise.
